# Card-audit puzzle (mtg-948 Part B) backing CLOSED issue mtg-399
# (Card Compatibility: Black Knight).
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. K:First Strike — a 2/2 first striker deals its combat damage in the
#      first-strike combat damage step (CR 702.7). Against a 2/2 ground
#      blocker with no first strike, Black Knight kills the blocker BEFORE it
#      can deal damage back, so Black Knight survives unscathed.
#   2. The 2/2 body connects / trades favorably in real games (the issue's
#      WORKING evidence). Protection-from-white is covered by the issue's
#      gameplay reproducer; here we pin the first-strike combat outcome.
#
# P1 at 5 life has a single 2/2 Grizzly Bears. If P1 blocks, first strike
# kills the Bears and Black Knight lives; if P1 does not block, Black Knight
# connects toward lethal. Either way Black Knight survives — asserted below.
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/audit_black_knight_first_strike.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
# The log shows a "First Strike Combat Damage" step and Black Knight surviving.

[metadata]
Name:Black Knight first strike survives the trade (audit mtg-399)
Goal:Win
Turns:7
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 attacks with a 2/2 first-strike Black Knight. P1 at 4 life has a lone 2/2 Grizzly Bears. First strike (CR 702.7) means Black Knight deals its 2 damage first; a blocking Bears dies before dealing damage back, so Black Knight survives. Two unblocked first-strike hits (2 each) are lethal from 4 life. Assertions confirm P0 wins, P1 took damage, and Black Knight is still on the battlefield at game end.

